
<p>There is well know tool in Linux called dd for disk transfer. For
example if I wanted to copy from /dev/sda to /dev/sdb I used to do:</p>

<pre class="example">
dd if=/dev/sda of=/dev/sdb
</pre>

<p>There is no need to use dd when a simple cat will do:</p>

<pre class="example">
cat /dev/sda &gt; /dev/sdb
</pre>

<p>Beside saving key strokes it copies <em>three</em> times faster!</p>

